latestPosts.caption:
“Real leadership isn’t about molding others to be like you—it’s about empowering them to be more of themselves.” 💯

When Daly City Mayor Dr. Rod Daus-Magbual chose me to represent the Asian-American community for the city’s AANHPI Heritage Month proclamation, that’s exactly what he did. He saw value in who I already was—in the work I’ve been doing in the community—and he used his platform to uplift that.

That’s the kind of leadership we need more of. Leaders who see you, back you, and push you forward without asking you to change who you are.

🕊️ In memory of @jomamathan RIP

Much love and gratitude to Mayor @rod4dalycity and to all those who lead with heart, humility, and vision. 

Shout out to Brother @whysf and Cousin @charmainecin for the introduction. 🌁🔗 

Let’s keep building each other up. ⚔️🆙

#LeadershipMatters #AANHPI #Representation #DalyCity #CommunityStrong

“You’re Asian—why do you talk like that?” Daly City Council shut that down real quick. 😂

If you’ve ever been told you don’t “sound” like your race, this one’s for you. Drop your story in the comments—and tag someone who can relate.

As a Filipino-American born and raised in San Francisco and Daly City, I’ve heard that line my whole life—especially from folks who aren’t from the Bay.

Let’s be real: it’s part of why my content hits the way it does.

Last week, I had the honor of representing the Asian American community during Daly City’s official proclamation of May 2025 as Asian American, Native Hawaiian, and Pacific Islander (AANHPI) Heritage Month.
I shared a bit of my story—and while the full dialogue was edited for time, the message stays true. 💯

Big love to Vice Mayor Glenn Sylvester and Councilmember Juslyn Manalo for making me feel SEEN. 🙏🏽

#DalyCity #SF #BayArea #AANHPI #FilipinoAmerican #RepresentationMatters

“Dude, you’re Asian. Why you talking like that?” 🌟 Tales of a Bay Area Kid 🎬 | Discovering My Identity Growing Up Filipino in SF-Daly City! 🇵🇭 

Relate? Like this post! And comment below.

🔥 The best burrito in SF might just be tucked away in the Excelsior District—three of my top five come from this side (my side) of town. This spot right here? Been in my foodie rotation since back in the day. The kind of place that reminds you why we fell in love with Frisco food in the first place. ❤️🌁

“Tell ‘em Adonis sent ya…” ™️

📍 @taqueriaguadalajarasf - 4798 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112

✍🏽 Have you been to Guad? What’s your order? Comment below. 

👉🏽 Did you know? The Mission-style burrito—while rooted in traditional Mexican flavors—is widely recognized as an American adaptation. Born in San Francisco’s Mission District in the 1960s and innovated by immigrants, the Super Burrito might just be more American than apple pie.

✨ What started as a humble neighborhood staple is now a national icon. And honestly? Few things feel more American to me than being born Asian 🇵🇭 in SF—and raised on Super Burritos. 🇺🇸🌯🇲🇽💯

“I’m interested in what it means to be an American. I’m interested in what it means to live in America. I’m interested in the kind of country that we live in and leave our kids. I’m interested in trying to define what that country is.” 

🎶 “Born in the U.S.A.” @springsteen 🫡

latestPosts.caption:
Since 1978, Zanze’s Cheesecake has been holding it down for San Francisco with the softest, most delicate cheesecake in the game—so airy you gotta cut it with fishing line. 🎣🍰 No hype, just tradition. No frills, just flavor. Real foodie locals know. ✊🏽

In May 2020, after nearly 43 years in the game, Zanze’s retail shop on Ocean Ave permanently closed. Mr. Sam Zanze, second-generation baker, hung up his apron and passed the whisk to the Duggan family—owners of SF institution @originaljoes.sanfrancisco @originaljoes.westlake 

The cheesecakes are still made in the OG bake shop, but now you can pick it up FRESH at @loj.market My wife grabbed me one for my birthday the other day. 😋

📍Little Original Joe’s Market, 393 West Portal Ave, San Francisco, CA 94127

👑 Named one of Food & Wine’s “Best Cheesecakes in America”
🥄 Minimal crust. Maximum legacy.

Do you recognize my inspiration for this video?

Tag someone who needs to try this Bay Area icon. Save this for your next celebration. 🍰❤️

#CheeseCake #BayAreaEats #SFFoodie #DessertLover #SF

“This Michelin Bib Gourmand spot serves Southeast Asian flavors through a California lens—and it’s right here in SF. 🔥 Foodies, don’t sleep!”

🌟Good Good Culture Club comes from the same crew behind Liholiho Yacht Club. Beyond the colorful space and rooftop vibes… it’s their values that spoke to me—diversity, equity, care, and empowerment. My day ones know how much that matters to me. So when it came time to spend my hard-earned money on a nice dinner with the fam… this just felt right. 🙌🏽

If this spot’s on your list, drop a 🔥 in the comments. Tag the crew you’d bring and hit save so you don’t forget.

📍 @goodgoodcultureclub 3560 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94110

Special shout out to @chefravikapur  and @thetastebud 😃🙌🏽
